4:
Allow me to cut to the chase: This is
a formal invitation. I would have you
visit my merchant vessel.
5:
You've all piqued my interest, and
my interests deserve appropriate
patronage.
9:
I look forward to your visit, my little
gum drops.Love, Quazer.
14:
Welcome to my humble ship. Please,
do make yourselves comfortable.
23:
Why do those children have collars
on their necks?! We won't stand for
this!
29:
But you can't pay your expenses
through adventure alone, can you?
Why else would you accept my
invitation?
32:
You can relax. These children are
here of their own accord, despite
what you may think.
35:
You may consider their presence as
evidence, evidence that I am a
sincere person.
38:
How can we come to an equitable
agreement if we are not honest with
one another? I already know much
of you, so now you shall grow
acquainted with me...
42: And my love of all things adorable.
44:
Well, come on then. I shall give you a
tour of the ship.
49:
Wow... If you sold one of these, you
could afford to feed thousands...
53:
Does that strike your fancy? Then all
that adorns this room is yours.
62:
These rocks lack cuteness, and
therefore have no value to me. The
sweet children, however, won't be
going anywhere.
65:
You, rabbit... You seem a bit
reluctant to do business with me.
71:
People are not pets. And I do not
desire the patronage of anyone who
would believe otherwise.
76:
There is no promise of wealth that
can tempt us.
80: Sorry. It IS all a little much...
84:
Don't worry your pretty little head. I
can understand your discomfort.
But it is what it is. When I see an
adorable neck, I ITCH to snap a
collar around it.
86:
And, Light... You have one of the
most adorable necks I've ever seen.
91:
You think me a helpless woodland
creature?
95:
Not JUST a woodland creature.
There's so much more to you. The
nobility, the powerlessness... When I
see you, I am overcome with joy.
97:
You want to save those kids, don't
you?
100:
You want to defeat me and break
their chains. But your wee arms
don't have the strength.
104:
Even if your allies best me, the
children will remain mine in spirit.
After all, they know where their
loyalties lie.
108:
Surely you recognize this. Fragile
souls need to feel controlled. They
cannot save themselves from their
own weakness.
112:
You are, truly, a wonderful hero. An
adorable, wonderful hero...
121:
All I suggest is that you act as you
see fit.Now, it seems we've gotten to
know each other. Shall we return?
127:
You will have my full patronage, on
the condition that Light
accompanies me from time to time.
131:
So if Light comes to hang out with
you, you'll give us money?
139:
Light, some things are more
important than money, we can
151:
It must be this way. Someone needs
to keep tabs on this nefarious
character...
154:
We shall take your deal. But I won't
be manipulated. No matter how
hard you push.
159:
I wouldn't dream of it, my adorable
little hero.
164:
There. Our contract is complete.
Now you shall never escape my
grasp.
